<h3>The Time-independent World Order</h3>

<p>I recently read two pieces a synthesis of which might be interpreted to say that all we can hope for in life is to concoct an artifice which distracts us from the impending and concurrent oblivion of purposelessness which would otherwise crush us.  This is not idle nihilistic navel gazing, though I'd understand if you couldn't tell the difference.</p>

<p>Herewith my earnest and hopefully readable attempt at such a synthetic enlightenment.</p>
